Subject: ESA-2010-003: EMC HomeBase Server Arbitrary File Upload Vulnerability

ESA-2010-003: EMC HomeBase Server Arbitrary File Upload Vulnerability


Identifier: ESA-2010-003

Identifier: HB6042

 
CVE Identifier: CVE-2010-0620

 
Severity Rating:  CVSS v2 Base Score: 9.3 (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)

 
Affected products:

EMC HomeBase Server version 6.2.x

EMC HomeBase Server version 6.3.x

 
Vulnerability Summary: 

EMC HomeBase Server contains a vulnerability that may allow an

unauthenticated remote user to upload arbitrary files on the affected

HomeBase Server.
 

Vulnerability Details: 

A flaw exists within the HomeBase SSL Service that may be exploited by

unauthenticated remote user to upload arbitrary files on the affected

HomeBase Server.  Successful exploitation may result in code execution

under the context of the service.

 
Problem Resolution: 

The following EMC HomeBase products contain resolutions to this issue:

.               EMC HomeBase 6.2.3 Server

.               EMC HomeBase 6.3.2 Server

 

EMC strongly recommends all customers upgrade to latest versions of the

products, which contain the resolution to this issue, at the earliest

opportunity.

 

Link to remedies: 

Registered EMC Powerlink customers can download software from Powerlink.

For HomeBase Software navigate in Powerlink to Home > Support > Software

Downloads and Licensing > Downloads E-I > HomeBase.

.               HomeBase Server 6.2.3.  Download the binaries for the
appropriate

operating system from the section HomeBase 6.2 SP3. This includes
Security

Vulnerability HB6042

.               HomeBase Server 6.3.2.  Download the binaries for the
appropriate

operating system from the section HomeBase 6.3 SP2. This includes
Security

Vulnerability HB6042

 

Because the view is restricted based on customer agreements, you may not

have permission to view certain downloads. Should you not see a software

download you believe you should have access to, follow the instructions
in

EMC Knowledgebase solution emc116045. 

 

